# Reversibility

- Deliver work as small, isolated commits with clear messages.
- Every new capability should be removable without breaking unrelated code.
- Prefer feature flags or optional modules over irreversible wiring.
- Add tests for new behavior so rollback is safe.
- Do not force-push or rewrite history without operator approval.
